gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Lakers 113, Knicks 105
gameRecap.excerpt: The Lakers defeated the Knicks, 113-105. LeBron James recorded 24 points, five rebounds, and five assists for the Lakers, with Austin Reaves adding 22 points (3-6 3PM), seven assists, and six rebounds in the victory. Jalen Brunson tallied 36 points, 10 assists, and six rebounds for the Knicks in the losing effort. The Lakers improve to 26-25, while the Knicks snap their nine-game winning streak and fall to 32-18.
